  <section id="our-support">
    <p>In Node.js, we're going to be working on supporting Black members of the community. If we can help - by using our collective platforms to amplify your words, by helping you in your career or in contributing to open-source, or in any other way - we are here for you. Each one of us in the list below has put out a message (linked) asserting our support and willingness to help - feel free to ping us in these threads, via open DMs on the linked accounts, or by sending us an email. We are here for you.</p>

    <section id="we-are-here-for-you">Tierney Cyren (<a href='https://twitter.com/bitandbang/status/1267893948149911556?s=20'>message of support</a>, <a href='https://twitter.com/bitandbang'>twitter</a>)</section>
    
    <section id="emails">Additionally, please feel welcome to reach out to the <a href="https://github.com/nodejs/node#tsc-technical-steering-committee">Node.js TSC members</a> and <a href="https://github.com/nodejs/community-committee#community-committee-members">Node.js Community Committee members</a> via our email addresses listed in the links, respectively.</section>
